post.body: It was a cash only club, their atm had run out of cash and we had none on us. Refunded cover for 12 of us.
everything's fine...nothing to see here...move along now....
ha! I took one at 6 the other day.
Thanks. There's nothing else I can erase though. I can't hold email messages or contacts on a memory card as far as I know.
For some reason now it only holds 20 email messages where before it held 1000s and I've changed nothing else.
great xmas party tonight. Fun people, tons of food and a wine I actually like. Thankfully kim remembers what I like cuz I never do.
Finally at my destination. Good to be out of the car.
Managed to go less than 5 miles in the last hour. Ugh.
Sitting in traffic and I'm not even halfway there.
Never thought I'd see a club give people their cover money back...until last night. amazing.
Thanks sixthman for including me in your holiday festivities and for not forcing me to do the thriller dance. kelly, you're my hero.

It's 65 and sunny at the lake. Perfect thanksgiving week!
Finally in atlanta. It feels so good to be home...hehe...home.
Accident on I-20. Been on the road for a week and today is the first day I've hit any traffic...2 accidents-before and after B'ham.
Glen show was great...heading back to tiff's now.
Just saw sara and sean watkins! Love them! Glen's up next...
Almost done with a 13+ hour driving day. Drove from one end of texas to the other. Tired.
Driving thru texas. Bigass rock hit my windshield. Now there's a bigass crack. I think I might hate texas or at least their bigass rocks.
Leaving Las Cruces, NM now. Driving across Texas today. Seeing Glen Phillips in Dallas with Tiff tomorrow. yay!
Today was longer than I expected. planned on hitting the road about 6 hours ago. I'm still in phx. should I stay tonight or go tomorrow???
My car holds a lot more than I thought...but still less than I hoped. need to pack a few more things, then I'm hittin' the road.
My place is almost ready for its new tenants. It even smells like freshly baked brownies.
Just ripped over 10Gs of music into my iTunes/iPod. I'm finally running out of space on my iPod. Time for an upgrade.
I work with the Coolest.People.Ever.
okay, crisis averted, kinda. thanks babs for putting it into perspective for me.
crap crap crap crap crap crap crap crap.....oh, and did i say crap?

Looking through photos from Christmas and realizing that I have both silly cousins and silly cousins-in-law and I love them all!
